gov.cms.qrda.validator.model

Class SchematronCategory

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.cms.qrda.validator.model.SchematronCategory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SchematronCategory
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The SchematronCategory class contains information describing a type of schematron file, which maps directly to a sub-directory underneath the major directories defined in the QRDA_HOME/qrda filespace. A SchematronCategory object is basically a definition of a directory under the schematron, testfile, isofile, vocabulary and results directories. Each spec contains the name of the directory on the disc, and the display name of the directory as shown in the UI. A lsit of the directory specs is serialized to disc and loaded into memory as needed.
    Author:
    Dan Donahue ESAC Inc.
